column1: 233006;instagram;2018-11-10 00:40:20;FALSE;"today marks the anniversary of my rape a year ago. it was a first date gone wrong. he insisted that we met at his apartment. i was hesitant
column2: should’ve listened to my first instinct. a couple glasses of chardonnay later
column4: he began to push himself onto me. i told him to stop
column5: he didn’t listen. he pushed and forced himself even harder
column6: eventually flipping me over and holding my wrists so tight in a way i’ll never forget. as he began to rip off my clothes
column8: i struggled and cried and tried scratching and pushing
column9: and he grabbed my struggling arms and held them behind my back. when i eventually broke free
column10: i hit my head on the coffee table on the fall to the hardwood floor. i pulled up my pants again
column12: coat & phone and ran outside where i continued to put myself back together with so many tears in my eyes that i had to walk my bike home because i couldn’t see well enough to ride it. but i am not a victim.... i am a #survivor and today i gave myself a permanent reminder of my strength and agility as i join thousands more with this symbol of unity. inspired by the strands of our dna
column13: mixed with a white rose to breathe life
column14: and a fiery shape to represent power. this tattoo was designed by @lostconversations for @ladygaga and the 50 survivors in the chorus that joined her onstage at the 2016 oscars. 1 in 2 women and 1 in 5 men will be sexually abused in their lifetime. you’re not as alone as you think... and i love you and i’m proud of you. ❤️

column1: 233112;instagram;2018-11-09 22:12:37;FALSE;"i've been sexually harassed multiple times while serving in chile... people would cat-call us all the time and they would say really dirty and gross stuff to my companion and i in english. i don't even know if they understand what they are saying. one individual informed me that ""i'd like to go to church with you... then go to your house with you... then go to canada with you."" oh my gosh
column4: i had an amazing experience in chile
column5: i wouldn't trade this experience with anything! most of the people there are so funny and nice and it was amazing to see people progress. despite working super hard we were unable to reap the fruits of our labour
column7: they would come to church and be willing to get baptized. right before baptism they would fall away. i felt that satan would work his way into their minds. we were a bit beaten down from these experiences since it has happened many times.

column3: not two but three different investigators called to let us know that they decided to cancel their baptismal date. it was devastating and i felt so heartbroken
column4: especially on my birthday. i know the lord gives people trials but despite this i didn't give up.

column2: i'm a perfectionist and going on a mission where i had to learn a different language and focus on studying the teachings of the bom was hard for me. i did not feel like myself at first and it was hard being unable to express myself in spanish. but through hard work
column3: i was slowly able to master the language. spiritually
column4: i learned the importance of the atonement and the commandments. i always like to say before i left
column5: i believe that the church/bom are true. now i know these things are true and i can't turn back from it.

column2: an idea from another man’s mind...

column1: frank ocean is one of my favorite music artists/songwriters.  he’s always got these one liners that keeps me deep in thought for days.  love this line cuz it makes me wonder if i’m living in an idea from another man’s mind...and not from my own.  sometimes we can place ourselves in these boxes
column2: these narrow ideas of what and how we should be.  some of its cuz of societal pressures
column3: some of its the need for acceptance
column4: and some of its just fear to be who we really are.  frank ocean’s one of those artists that is completely out his box both personally and musically and i think that’s what makes his songs so dope.  it’s never just one kind of way.

column1: this is what i love about music (or the arts in general) and what i love about writing songs.  as a writer you can’t fake it...people will know when you are.  you gotta get out your box and be willing to risk being you.  i hope to be that kind of artist...one that inspires people to stop living from another man’s mind...and start living from their own. 🌟✨💫

column1: 233160;instagram;2018-11-09 21:45:43;FALSE;"between my second and third year of university i had to take a year long medical leave. i then took more time off and traveled to india and nepal where i continued on my quest of healing. i found yoga
column3: and rediscovered my true passions in life. up till not too long ago
column4: very few people knew about this. i was terrified of what people would have thought if they were to find out. in the last moth i’ve been working on my grad school personal statement which has forced me to be vulnerable and talk about that year and the half i took for myself and for my health. writing about it made me realize how
column5: though it was one of the hardest moments of my life
column6: it is because of it that i am now able to pursue this journey of higher education. this experience left me with a burning desire to learn and research more effective treatment for survivors and other people struggling. despite the initial fears that talking about this subject brought up
column7: it has welcomed so much connection and healing into my life. turns out that more people than i could have ever imagined also went or are currently going through something similar: taking time to heal and fighting to reclaim their life back. today i feel thankful
column8: and so very hopeful. to all of you who are fighting your own personal battle: your healing will bring you purpose

column1: 233224;instagram;2018-11-09 20:22:10;FALSE;"this is my first baby and i was a terrible parent. i didn't play with her. i didn't listen to her when she was afraid and confused.⠀
your child-self is your first baby. this baby girl went through a lot all alone. traumas and disappointments no child should experience. she started to believe that the world was an unsafe place
column3: talents and joys close & behind closed doors. as an adult
column4: i thought that if i just forgot about her then the challenges that she faced would automagically go away... i was wrong

column1: she is alive and well in me every single day as your child-self is alive within you. ⠀
when you feel fear stopping you from stepping out of your comfort zone
column5: 9 or 14 year old self that learned to stop trusting. learned that they had to be perfect. worried that they would lose love or be attacked if they put themselves out there. ⠀

column1: things shift when your first baby girl finally gets your attention. she becomes an ally in your joy. my clients have had so many epiphanies simply by turning their lens to this part of themselves.⠀

column2: check in with her. ask her what she is afraid of and let her know that you got it now.  let her know she can trust you and that the new things you are trying are fun and adventurous - then approach those new things that way - with a sense of fun and adventure. let her know it is safe to come out and play again. your life will be more joyful
column3: abundant and fun when you do. ase. 💝💝💝⠀

column2: does for your inner little miss get to play in your life?⠀

column1: 233296;instagram;2018-11-09 18:51:28;FALSE;"you know what i do when i don’t want to show up? i look back! 👀
cause man even after doing this day in and day out i still have to have a stern talk with myself from time to time.

when i was just starting i envisioned how i wanted things to be.  i thought about what it would feel like to look in the mirror and actually like myself again.  i used the thoughts of what i would feel like eventually if i just did it even when i didn’t want to.
it never gets easier to show up but it certainly gets easier to look back and know that we’re not going that way.

233305;instagram;2018-11-09 18:57:00;FALSE;"pink elephant- a couple days ago @kathrinenarducci (artist and actress extraordinaire) posted a picture of a #pinkelephant she bought. it reminded me of a song i wrote a few years ago called ""pink elephant"". i had been reading a story to my nephew who was about three years old at the time. the line in the book said
column2: ""it takes a lot of paper to gift wrap an elephant"". that line made me very sad and it stuck with me. a few days later i woke up in the middle of the night and recorded the song. when i performed it live there were many tears in the audience. it is just a reminder that we all have sadness and secrets and stories that hurt our hearts and that we are ashamed to tell. for me it comes out in my music and art. others don't have outlets. if we recognized that we all have our ""pink elephants"" perhaps we would be kinder and gentler with one another. it can be a cruel world sometimes. #elephantintheroom #addiction #abuse #metoo #femalemusician #liveperformance #cello";;en;#pinkelephant

column1: 233331;instagram;2018-11-09 18:11:47;FALSE;"are you listening to the believed podcast? episode 2 - “how he got away” perfectly explains this problem as we hear the story of brianne randall-gay. brianne was the first person to report larry nassar to the police way back in 2004.
if we tell kids we will believe them
column2: then the justice system the child meets when they report has to be trained and accountable for believing and defending them.

column1: what are the consequences of the triangle of trauma?
👉 an abuser is not only vindicated but empowered. many times the record does not even show an arrest. the record will show that there was a charge against the abuser but that it was dismissed.
👉 professionals have now proven to the child their abuser was right - the abuser is more powerful and the child will not be believed.
👉 sometimes the child is even put back in the care of the abuser.
👉 families can be torn apart by who to believe - the record now shows  the abuser was wrongfully accused.
👉 the child and the entire community is put at risk.
👉 who feels responsible for all of this - the child. sarah wrote about this from a child’s perspective in “it is not your crime” (link in bio)
👉 the exact opposite of the original intention to help the child by reporting has happened.
reporting child sexual abuse should be the first step to help a child heal and thrive.💞

column1: #michelleobama has just revealed that she had a miscarriage prior to conceiving her 2 daughters via ivf. it’s a new season of openness and sharing hidden struggles and we are so proud of the women and men around the world opening up about formally taboo topics.
in the interview with #robinroberts which aired today
column2: former first lady michelle opened up about this for the first time. 'i felt like i failed because i didn’t know how common miscarriages were because we don’t talk about them
column3: ' she said. 'we sit in our own pain
column4: thinking that somehow we’re broken...that’s one of the reasons why i think it’s important to talk to young mothers about the fact that miscarriages happen.' her memoir #becoming is out soon.

column1: living in an other culture you encounter many things that are strange to you
column2: because you were not raised with it being “normal”. some of these cultural difference are funny and pleasant like the two kiss framing an accounted
column3: or the long meals ending with cheese. and then there are these differences that just feel wrong.

column1: when my daughter gets called a poupée it feels wrong each and every time.
i know that it’s meant in a sweet way. it’s like saying “my love”. it has a nice sound and french people have learnt this word to be positive.
from the first time i heard my mother in law say this word to my daughter it just made a bad feeling in my stomach area. that was even before i tracked back
i just couldn’t understand why you would want to call a girl puppet? especially now that there is a general raising of consciousness with the help of #metoo. we understand now
column2: that girls can have a hard time being used and over powered. so why wound you want to call your girl puppet? a puppet is an object that is passive and moved in what ever way desired. there is no own will
column3: only a nice smilling face that comforts.

column1: we think for months for the right name for our children
column3: read name origin stories and take care of current name trends.

column1: calling your child with nicknames has a similar effect than a name. we speak to them through the shape and sound of a word. and especially through meaning.
for me a name is like an ally for us. we are literally named by it. i am named by clara
column2: and yes clarity became my program. i am a coach and help people getting into clarity.

column3: how we raise them. we do our best- all of us

column644: men samtidigt ger undersökningen bottenbetyg till utbildningsväsendet . att endast 63 % av killarna är positivt inställda till lagen samtidigt som 33 % av killarna/männen tror att det är samtycke att lägga sig en säng naken med någon . 17 % av männen tror även att det automatiskt föreligger samtycke om man är ihop eller om man går hem med någon sent på kvällen . ♂️ alla som pratat om att det är en liten klick som begår övergrepp har här

column1: there was a lilac bush here. i loved the smell. i picked them for my mom and she put them in water.
he was my crush. two grades older. i played hide-and-seek with my friends one day and hid inside the lilac bush.

he cornered me. his face close to my face. i can still feel his presence. ""i'm going to get you naked."" my body filled with cement as he crawled out and left me forever different. i never told anyone. i didn't know i could.
i was a child. he was a child.
and this still haunts me every day
column2: but i'm finally going to free myself from this.

andré henriques , bárbara barradas , cátia moreso , inês simões , marco alves dos santos e sónia alcobaça coro teatro nacional de são carlos e orquestra sinfónica pouguesa cenário henrique ralheta figurinos rafaela mapril desenho de luz luís duae assistência de encenação rafael gomes e diana vaz produção executiva força de produção coprodução teatro da trindade inatel , teatro nacional de são carlos e temporada darcos paindo conto tradicional macaco de rabo coado , canção bandido imagina uma personagem que não é um macaco mas um advogado , casanova dos tempos modernos , homem que acumula conquistas e vai trocando por novas conquistas , sem pensar muito nas consequências dos seus atos . casanovismo e donjuanismo são revisitados numa época em que guerras dos sexos ( ou dos géneros ) já não são que eram , ou têm pelo menos discursos e legitimidades diferentes . coros gregos e essencialismos em tempos digitais e de em quem devemos acreditar : libreto , nos protagonistas , nos antagonistas , ou nas personagens que , falando em vez de notar , contestam estes diálogos , estes tipos , esta dialética ? de d. giovanni à música pop , dos bordões linguísticos aos jogos nonsense , personagens de « canção bandido » trazem para palco tudo que lhes ocorre , tudo que sirva suas estratégias ou ilustra suas dúvidas . e os espectadores , ceamente , tomam paido . classificação etária | column1: 233715;instagram;2018-11-09 12:39:38;FALSE;"enligt undersökningen uppger nästan nio av tio unga att man känner till den nya lagen. där har vi på väldigt kort tid lyckats. men denna undersökning ger bottenbetyg till utbildningsväsendet (och till oss föräldrar/vuxna som är nära barn/killar). att endast 63% av killarna är positivt inställda till lagen samtidigt som 33% av killarna/männen anser att det är samtycke om man lägger sig naken med någon. 17% av männen tror även att det automatiskt föreligger samtycke om man är ihop eller om man går hem med någon sent på kvällen.

column3: ett tydligt svar på att så inte är fallet. tydligare än såhär blir det inte. siffrorna skiljer sig även markant mellan tjejer & killar. däremot har männens syn på samtycke fått råda
column4: både i sängen & i rätten. nu har vi fått nog. vi
column6: har ändrat lagen och pratat ut om män som inte inhämtat samtycke.

column1: det som behövs nu är såklart
column2: som jag sagt aldeles för länge
column3: ett enormt samtyckeslyft. som även riktar sig specifikt till killar.

column9: eller det lilla stödet civilsamhället kan söka av dem. det behövs mkt mer! snälla se detta som det haveri det är. ni vet mkt väl hur allvarligt staten skulle ta på detta om det var 100 män om dagen som blev våldtagna. över 500 män om dagen som blev utsatta för- eller- försök till sexualbrott. kom igen nu!

column1: مطلب از پیج فیسبوک ""دنیای مردان، رویای زنان""
نتیجه ی عدالت جنسیت محور و زن محور چنین صحنه هاییه! زنی مردی رو می زنه و بعد تمارض به آسیب دیدن می کنه و در نتیجه پلیس مرد رو دستگیر می کنه! مرد هم کتک می خوره و هم بی گناه مجازات میشه!
البته اون فمینیست هایی که این قوانین رو تصویب می کنن به هدفشون رسیده اند! مهم اینه که زن تونسته انتقام بگیره و به زن آسیبی نرسه! اینکه چه بلایی سر مرد میاد دیگه واسه شون موضوعیت نداره

column1: 233736;instagram;2018-11-09 11:48:32;FALSE;"(suite) « pourquoi ai-je mis 15 ans avant d’en parler? »
💬 le fait que ce soit un membre de ma famille à certainement joué en sa faveur concernant mon silence. il est d’autant plus difficile de dénoncer un proche qu’un inconnu. si on parle
column2: c’est la famille entière qui est affectée
column3: qui « explose ». alors que si on ne parle pas tout reste « normal »

column2: quand j’ai compris que ce qu’il m’avait fait ce qualifiait de « pédophilie »
column4: et « d’agression sexuelle » j’ai continué de « choisir » (le choisit-on réellement ?) le mutisme. pourtant durant mon adolescence : je n’avais plus peur de lui
column5: je pensais que ma parole avait plus de poids que celle d’un enfant… mais la culpabilité restait
column6: et la honte s’y était greffée. la culpabilité
column7: non pas dans le sens où je pensais toujours que c’était « à cause de moi »
column8: je savais qu’il méritait qu’une chose : payer pour ses crimes. la culpabilité dans le sens où : si j’en parle je vais détruire ma mère
column10: mes grands-parents (mon bourreau n’entre pas en compte). je pensais à toutes les personnes que j’emmenais avec moi si je parlais. toutes celles qui souffriraient « de ma faute »
column11: une fois de plus. bien que nous sachions que ce n’est pas de la faute à la victime. si je parlais
column13: de peine et douleur. je me disais « j’ai réussi « à vivre » 10 ans avec
column14: alors pourquoi pas le reste de ma vie après tout ? autant épargner ma famille ».

column2: mes parents s’étaient séparés en mauvais termes. je vivais avec ma mère. j’avais peur qu’en parlant
column3: mon père pense que ce soit juste pour « foutre la merde ».

column1: 233805;instagram;2018-11-09 09:43:17;FALSE;"invite me to your wedding i’m a walking talking point.
in all seriousness though i used to dress like this
column2: or a more toned down version of it
column3: regularly. i stopped completely after the events of the past year. a constant stream of objectification in an environment it shouldn’t feature will do that to you.

column1: i’m not alone in this reaction
column2: i’ve read accounts from others who dropped makeup
column5: or certain hairstyles out of their regular attire in an attempt to control how they were perceived and treated by men.

column1: none of it works. if men won’t control themselves there is little you can do once they’ve fixed you in the cognitive compartment labelled “thing”. my clothing choices used to be a matter of “oh you’ve decided i’m a girl
column2: i’m going to take that to an extreme.” a gender non-conforming ex-girlfriend of mine once told me that because i ‘can’ look normal i should look normal.

as someone always othered on sight she had her reasons for wanting to protect me from the same. but shortly after leaving that relationship i didn’t really hold back. this is a signature style of mine now
column3: not able to be unentangled from “me” at all in the eyes of many.

column1: i knew no one at this wedding except my partner
column3: and the couple getting married. my partner was one of the groomsmen
column4: leaving me with no one i knew to sit with. normally this would have caused me a lot of anxiety but that’s the advantage of being a walking talking point; you’re never short on people to chat to. even better for me; the fashion is a special interest
column7: and cats are a special interest.

column1: there’s noise and strangers and small talk and i have to wear a bra
column3: and then there’s a last minute venue change. i can’t overstate how much i keep myself going through all that with this elaborately gendered performance.

column1: i’m good at it. who doesn’t like doing what they are good at.
i don’t show up like this without asking
column2: but no one has ever said no. the directive for today was “more is more”

column5: supposedly suppressed gender and i am tired.

column1: i call those affected by sexual violence ""survivors."" i have spent the better part of a year waiting to feel some magical transition from ""victim"" to ""survivor
column2: as if one day i would conquer the key to stopping all of the immeasureable pain havoc wreaked on my life. truthfully
column3: i have yet to feel like a survivor. on most days
column4: i feel robbed and like i am grieving for a version of myself that i am not sure exists anymore. but more importantly
column5: every victim/survivor deserved the right to claim whatever term makes then feel the most comfortable or more accurately represents their feelings.

column2: we must use our language intentionally. something bad did not happen to me. someone did something bad to me. that someone raped me. it was not an accident

column1: it is up to us to frame our trauma because unfortunately the rest of the world will not do it for us
column2: or will do so with victim blaming and stigma. .

column1: 233850;instagram;2018-11-09 08:35:25;FALSE;all my life i was supported by a loving family but i craved for more. i couldn’t understand what was going on in my head. i felt like every letter
column3: every word spoken was a threat to me. i was calling out for help but didn’t let no one in. this is something we all do throughout our life regardless of what’s going on. we push family & friends away from us often hurting them because we are hurting and feel they don’t understand or help us enough. my life was spent locking myself into a small room constantly searching for help but never finding it. i couldn’t understand how come google had no help for me. it puzzled me so much so that i felt worse because i now felt that if no one bothered about people like me with a bodily disfigurement then i shouldn’t exist in society. everyday i hear young people talking about how they don’t receive the support they need and when my power grows i will do all i can to help make that change. i no longer feel that anyone should be left out in society or under represented. i felt like that for too long but today i’m thriving and i’m here to support anyone who needs me ❣️ #metoomovement #metoo #timesup #inclusion #diversityandinclusion #equalityrights #mindset #confidence #supportus #bopo #bopowarrior #thriver #thriver4life #loveandrespect @nunude_official ❤️;;en;#metoomovement

column1: we are standing up & speaking out about the issues we have faced during our journey/stay at miss earth 2018. we have brought this to your attention and social medias as we feel miss lorraine and the organisation have turned their heads at our cry for help. as most of you now know i was the first person to speak up personally to lorraine on the 14th october regarding my issues and concerns about amado cruiz a sponsor to the pageant. straight after i voiced my concerns to miss lorraine miss canada 2018 also spoke to her regarding her thoughts and encounters with the miss earth sponsor and how the miss earth pageant was contradicting with the use of plastic bottles and single use plastics & our carbon footprint etc whilst being away. miss lorraine promised to act upon the issues with amado the sponsor and said he would be banned from all events myself and miss canada attended. so you can imagine how shocked we were to see his attendance at prejudging events and even the coronation night of miss earth 2018. he should have been removed and banned from all contact with the organisation. i did not sign up for sexual harassment i signed up to represent my beautiful country with pride at an ecological pageant whereby i wanted to promote my advocacy and further plans to protect our precious mother earth. i am 100% a green queen & eco queen i have been campaigning and implementing change to protect mothers earth since 2014 and shall continue to do so for as long as i can. i am so grateful to have the backing of my national director who acted upon this issue straight away once notified

column5: previous national director of miss earth & my wonderful filipino fans and family who i adore and couldn’t have spoken up without!! i will always love the philippines for supporting me and checking up on my safety during and after the finals! i will not let this incident tarnish my thoughts and feeling towards filipinos. this was an individual act! •

233869;instagram;2018-11-09 09:01:16;FALSE;remember not every time u get targeted is because u “deserve” it or u “deserved” it.karma shoukd not be used as a convenient excuse for someone else’s filthy behavior.when u catch few minutes with  yourself in ur busy chaotic life and the questions don’t stop hurling themselves at you.again and again...the scenes replaying in ur mind fresh the wounds column2: statistics show that one in four girls will be sexually abused before they turn 18 years old.
sex crimes are just as taboo as mental health issues. there are child predators
column4: and rapist who roam amongst us. as a community
column5: we hear the stories and “shamaraat (rumors)” and we continue to associate with these individuals and bring them around our children. we would much rather believe that our people do not sexually assault and abuse children. this is the furthest thing from the truth because i personally know several woman who were raped or sexually assaulted by a south sudanese man. statistically
column6: only 12% of child sexual abuse is ever reported to the authorities. many people go through life keeping their assault a secret and dealing with the aftermath of it in silence
column7: just read this story below! feel free to comment your thoughts and advice on her story! please keep in mind that she will be reading you comments
column8: so please be kind and appropriate.

column1: ______________________________________________________________and to the girl who trusted me enough to share her story
column2: thank you! thank you for having the strength and courage to share your story. i know the journey to recovery will be a long one but i have faith that one day you will be able to look back at this traumatic experience
column3: and not feel the weight of the mental and emotional pain sitting on your shoulders. please understand that you are not the only one
column4: baby girl. #metoo because there are many more woman who have gone through what you’ve gone through. i know it’s hard but you will get through this pain. your story will inspire many. always
column5: always ask for help and talk to someone because the suffering in silence has to end. take care

column1: 233954;instagram;2018-11-09 05:04:48;TRUE;;"det är dags och stå upp och protestera mot den bristande vården för kvinnor efter graviditet. nu får det räcka!! #diastasupproret börjar nu!! in och följ @diastasupproret och dela allt ni kan. nu måste politikerna vakna och inser vilket enormt problem detta är. se vad vi gjorde med #metoo i fjol. nu gör vi det igen för att tillsammans är vi starka👊🏻

jag har liksom många av er andra mycket besvär av min diastas och får som det ser ut just nu ingen hjälp av landstinget. men alla som känner mig vet att jag är rätt envis så jag tänker intr ge upp än. jag har länge vart frustrerad över att vården inte tar oss på allvar. jag fick nog och startade diastasupproret på instagram och skriver även en del om det på min blogg. min ambition med @diastasupproret upproret är att vi ska få en gemensam plattform där vi kan se till att göra våra röster hörda och kräva rätten till vård. oavsett om den vården består av att få hjälp med rätt träning eller operation!

column1: 233995;instagram;2018-11-09 04:28:01;FALSE;"qanon fans are applying this same participatory behavior that we have celebrated in fiction fandom to real-world political drama. and why not? the boundaries between politics and entertainment have been collapsing for years. the entire trump presidency operates like reality tv
column2: completely divorced from any real stakes or substance.

column1: that’s what makes this all so terrifying. do these people really believe that tom hanks and hillary clinton are personally running a massive pedophilia ring? really??? but consider this: trump announced at a rally this week that the farmers being harmed by his stupid trade war had told him “we can take it.” no actual farmers said that to him. we all know that. but it’s a little thing
column2: just part of the story we are all interacting with.

column1: the pulsating heart of the qanon theory is not a lunatic fringe denying the real consequences of a failing presidency. the heart of it is a devoted fan base constructing elaborate theories to make the story more fun and engaging. and if you start from the premise that nothing government does matters
column2: then it’s easy to come along for the ride. there’s no real difference between hillary clinton and the smoke monster. they’re both just characters on the television.

column1: that’s what alarms me most about the growth of qanon. it’s not that these people are unhinged and possibly armed. it’s that we’ve lost the capacity to treat civics
column3: and public affairs as though they have actual stakes with actual consequences. the premise of the trump presidency is that nothing matters
column4: so you should root for your side and heckle the opposing team. he encourages his supporters to treat democrats and journalists like a rival fan base.
